HEADWORD: Tweed
<hw>Tweed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably a corruption
of <ets>twills</ets>. See <er>Twill</er>.]</ety> <def>A soft and
flexible fabric for men's wear, made wholly of wool except in some
inferior kinds, the wool being dyed, usually in two colors, before
weaving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

